Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.98,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Kometo Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.40,0:00:07.40,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,The river dries up during this season.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:08.98,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What a filthy bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.37,0:00:12.91,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,The railing's completely black.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.91,0:00:14.99,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.24,0:00:19.04,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to show you \Non the other side of the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.04,0:00:19.67,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.67,0:00:20.91,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.82,0:00:24.67,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go to the shopping \Narea near the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.67,0:00:26.02,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.02,0:00:27.67,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.96,0:00:35.61,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.61,0:00:36.68,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.09,0:00:38.10,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:39.39,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.70,0:00:41.85,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.73,0:00:57.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.55,0:00:59.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With brilliant detective \Nskills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:01.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An incident begins with a glowing toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.99,0:01:04.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A chance meeting leads to a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.31,0:01:08.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.11,0:01:10.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:56.04,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}The Mysterious Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:52.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,“The Mysterious Boy!”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.45,0:03:02.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys going to look \Nfor UFOs again tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:03.98,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.98,0:03:05.91,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We've already gone twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.33,0:03:08.54,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,And came up empty-handed both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.54,0:03:11.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're sure it'll show up tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.72,0:03:12.79,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.30,0:03:15.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,UFOs, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:18.73,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you don't believe in them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:22.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There have been three sightings \Nsince the month started!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.01,0:03:23.14,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.14,0:03:26.63,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,And they were all at the \Nriverbed near Kometo Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.63,0:03:31.47,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Some glowing gold thing flew \Nover the riverbed really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:32.31,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:36.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Some people even saw aliens on the riverbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.02,0:03:38.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,As detectives, we can't just \Nignore these sightings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.17,0:03:41.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Investigating aliens isn't a detective's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.74,0:03:44.08,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we're going tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.43,0:03:46.33,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:47.52,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.52,0:03:49.83,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagai Toys's curtains are open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:53.92,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's opening his store back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:03:59.79,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.79,0:04:02.93,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,This shop closed down a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.61,0:04:05.98,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I came here a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.98,0:04:09.80,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,A nice old couple ran the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.80,0:04:13.35,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But there was never much that I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.55,0:04:16.36,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,All they had were old toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.29,0:04:19.53,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:20.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.73,0:04:21.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.94,0:04:23.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:25.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your hands are covered in ice cream!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.99,0:04:27.61,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.61,0:04:29.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, now I'm all sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.39,0:04:37.25,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Even kids still care about this place, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:37.25,Tsutomu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oshiro Tsutomu (30) \NKuromaru Finance Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:41.84,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That kid with the glasses was \Nstaring at this toy engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.15,0:04:43.01,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:44.01,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.52,0:04:46.47,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't surprise me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.72,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You made me drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.51,0:04:54.27,Tokujiro,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nagai Tokujiro (72) \NManager of Nagai Toys
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:51.48,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Just leave that old thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:54.27,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My wife treasured this engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:58.30,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you should sell \Nthis place for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.76,0:05:00.57,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:03.63,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.63,0:05:04.74,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:06.66,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.80,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but in exchange,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:11.41,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,will you at least leave \Nsome incense in the altar?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:15.16,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time for that shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:16.85,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.85,0:05:17.98,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.61,0:05:19.26,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:20.67,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.10,0:05:23.42,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,You said you like liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:25.08,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.97,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that high quality scotch?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:30.92,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it when I went \Nto England with my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.92,0:05:33.31,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,And I've stopped drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.84,0:05:36.33,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.23,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.05,0:05:45.15,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'll be back once I \Nget the paperwork together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:46.76,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:56.08,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. That brat...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:00.69,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.69,0:06:02.08,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going out, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:04.58,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,We need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.58,0:06:06.16,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.16,0:06:07.59,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.59,0:06:09.18,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:18.41,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,The river dries up during this season.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.41,0:06:19.98,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What a filthy bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:23.56,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,The railing's completely black.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.03,0:06:25.98,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:29.97,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to show you \Non the other side of the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.97,0:06:30.58,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.58,0:06:31.91,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:35.66,DCMain,OSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go to the shopping \Narea near the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.90,0:06:37.16,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:38.66,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.17,0:06:44.54,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:46.67,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That was definitely the UFO.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.67,0:06:49.30,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It came from over the bridge \Nand landed over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:50.66,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.66,0:06:53.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.81,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Me, neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:06:59.16,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,The light disappeared around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.16,0:06:59.65,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:00.89,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:02.31,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.31,0:07:04.01,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's near the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:04.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:05.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a UFO.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.50,0:07:08.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:11.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:13.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:18.08,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Edogawa-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:22.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.17,0:07:27.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And, Haibara, call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:28.38,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:34.80,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Oshiro Tsutomu, thirty years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.44,0:07:38.81,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,He worked for Kuromaru Finance in Haido-cho.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.32,0:07:41.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He was a debt collector for \Na black market lender, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:42.81,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:47.67,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,According to security cameras in the \Nshopping center, he left the station after four,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.67,0:07:51.24,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,and walked past the shopping \Ncenter heading directly this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.50,0:07:55.32,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably came here to collect on a debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:07:56.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:07:58.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:03.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,it's likely he got drunk \Nand fell off this bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:07.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But just to be sure, go check \Nwith Kuromaru Finance tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.16,0:08:07.96,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:13.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So you kids came here to see the UFO?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.17,0:08:13.72,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:18.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear any suspicious sounds \Nor see any suspicious figures?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.73,0:08:20.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.28,0:08:23.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's likely that this was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:26.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Once we're finished with \Nthe general inspection—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.21,0:08:26.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:27.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.18,0:08:30.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a coupon for half off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.02,0:08:34.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,at a ramen shop in this man's wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:34.57,Ramen,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Shinobiya Ramen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.31,0:08:39.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been desperate to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.94,0:08:43.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,at Shinobiya Ramen if he \Nprinted out a coupon for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.46,0:08:45.54,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:47.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This bridge doesn't lead
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:50.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,to Shinobiya Ramen near \Nthe station shopping center.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:54.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He probably meant to go another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:57.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No, the coupon expires today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:57.59,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Effective Through August 13
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.29,0:09:02.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means he probably \Nmeant to stop by after work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:07.96,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Then it doesn't make sense \Nthat he came this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.08,0:09:13.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So if he was finished with work, \Nhe wouldn't have come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:16.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And if he wasn't, then he \Nwouldn't have been drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.85,0:09:18.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.33,0:09:27.50,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.61,0:09:47.81,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.81,0:10:09.76,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.76,0:10:12.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I live around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:15.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot my house key, and I can't get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:17.59,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Where are your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:19.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.26,0:10:21.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can I stay here until they come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:23.51,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.50,0:10:26.36,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.36,0:10:28.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently someone died at Kometo Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:30.77,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,A person?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.77,0:10:33.90,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,That explains the sirens I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.21,0:10:36.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it's a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.50,0:10:39.33,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,This is becoming a dangerous area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.33,0:10:40.20,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:41.70,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,You can come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:43.91,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,You can wait in here for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:45.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:52.03,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.29,0:10:53.56,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.74,0:10:59.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,These “Flashing Boomerangs” \Nbrings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:02.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You hardly see them anymore, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.59,0:11:05.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.55,0:11:06.32,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:09.06,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I had it out on a shelf, but it fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.50,0:11:11.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that shelf?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.08,0:11:11.98,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:16.50,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,My hand slipped when I tried to \Npick it up, and I dropped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.87,0:11:17.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:20.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, do you live alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:23.49,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, my wife passed away last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.59,0:11:27.74,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,She'd been in the hospital for a \Nlong time with a difficult disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.37,0:11:30.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And you've been alone since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:31.37,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.24,0:11:36.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone visit you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.38,0:11:38.82,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,No, nobody came.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.82,0:11:41.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been here the whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.38,0:11:44.26,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was here all day today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:45.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.13,0:11:54.65,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.25,0:11:57.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do your shoulders hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:11:59.84,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,From about six months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.84,0:12:02.78,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,They hurt pretty badly when \NI try to lift my arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:05.66,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:09.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The bottom half of this \Ncabinet has been cleaned,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.46,0:12:11.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the top is covered in dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:15.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might have \Ntrouble raising your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.43,0:12:17.50,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:20.17,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard cleaning the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.81,0:12:23.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you couldn't have \Npicked up the toy engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:24.18,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:27.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That shelf is pretty high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:30.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get the toy engine when \Nyour shoulders are hurting you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:34.23,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped it because I \Npushed myself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.83,0:12:37.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:39.13,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,No reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.13,0:12:42.50,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Being here alone just brought \Nback some old memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.90,0:12:46.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But someone must've visited you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.76,0:12:49.10,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.10,0:12:51.47,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:53.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because there's shoe polish on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.55,0:12:55.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.56,0:12:58.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the floor over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:00.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See those brown marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.48,0:13:06.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's shoe polish, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.08,0:13:13.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the person who died on the \Nbridge was wearing brown shoes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:16.71,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,An insurance salesman came this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:19.27,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,The shoe polish probably belongs to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.79,0:13:23.64,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I had him leave immediately since I \Nwasn't interested in his insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.64,0:13:25.78,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'd forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:29.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,These marks were made when \Nsomeone put these shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:33.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That means he took off his \Nshoes and came inside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.43,0:13:36.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you let him in when you \Nweren't interested in his insurance?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:40.96,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Son, your parents have \Nprobably come home by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.96,0:13:43.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, smell my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.44,0:13:45.01,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Son, that's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.01,0:13:46.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:54.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it smell like strawberries?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.07,0:13:55.56,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.82,0:13:57.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This evening my friend touched \Nthe door of this building
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.82,0:14:00.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with his strawberry ice cream covered hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.32,0:14:04.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I just touched it when I \Ntried to open the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.39,0:14:05.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so I smell like strawberries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:07.72,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.72,0:14:09.45,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll clean it in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:13.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This same smell was on the \Nhand of the man who died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:16.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He came here today, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:19.62,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you trying to say, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.62,0:14:24.13,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like you think I'm \Ninvolved in the case somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:25.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:28.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the one who killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.22,0:14:32.16,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:35.12,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're right,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:38.89,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,that means you're alone with a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.16,0:14:40.77,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that scare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:42.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.95,0:14:45.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,because I don't think \Nyou're actually a bad man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:02.36,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you say, \NI haven't killed anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.36,0:15:06.16,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, didn't he accidentally \Nfall from the bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.49,0:15:09.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You threw this off the bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.12,0:15:13.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and while the dead man was \Ndistracted, you pushed him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:17.96,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think a toy boomerang \Nwould fly that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.96,0:15:21.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You experimented numerous \Ntimes at the riverbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.79,0:15:25.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to see how the boomerang would \Nshine and how it would fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.93,0:15:29.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The people who saw that \Nstarted saying it was a UFO.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:31.35,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,A UFO?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.35,0:15:34.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,My friends were talking about it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.24,0:15:36.02,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:38.66,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, why would I go \Nthrough all that trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:41.54,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,just to push someone off a bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.09,0:15:44.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The man who died was young and fit,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.38,0:15:47.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so you couldn't overpower him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.45,0:15:50.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, your shoulders hurt, \Nso you can't lift your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.15,0:15:55.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You had to lift his legs while \Nhe was distracted by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.18,0:15:59.06,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know I lifted his legs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:02.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,His pants didn't have any grime \Nfrom the railing on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.97,0:16:06.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But his palms were pitch black with dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.54,0:16:09.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That proves he was holding the \Nrailing and leaning out over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:12.82,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't prove I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:16.69,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I would never do anything as \Nviolent as killing a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.69,0:16:20.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any shops that sell \Nthese boomerangs these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.58,0:16:22.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But there are plenty here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.24,0:16:24.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the strawberry ice cream...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.00,0:16:26.55,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:28.63,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.02,0:16:32.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then how did you know he fell off the bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.45,0:16:35.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I only said a man died near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.04,0:16:39.97,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural to think they fell \Nif a person died at a bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:43.98,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,He drank too much scotch \Nand accidentally fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:45.46,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's obviously—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:51.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know the victim \Nwas drinking scotch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:54.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not beer or ordinary whiskey,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.62,0:16:55.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but scotch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.51,0:16:59.01,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.72,0:17:01.49,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,had a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:10.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.54,0:17:14.19,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's missing some parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.19,0:17:16.61,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a small gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.96,0:17:18.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you try looking for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:19.39,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:24.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Think back on the moment the toy engine fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:37.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't the gear fall into a shoe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.84,0:17:42.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The police don't think it was \Nan accidental death, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:45.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They'll find out that the dead man
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.22,0:17:47.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,came here before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.66,0:17:51.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, if they find \Nthe gear in his shoe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:56.84,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,My wife was in the hospital \Na long time for her sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:17:59.18,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,It was expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.86,0:18:02.64,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up borrowing money \Nfrom some shady lenders
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.64,0:18:05.41,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,to pay her medical bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:09.49,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,The man who fell from the \Nbridge was a debt collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:12.06,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,He was terrible to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.80,0:18:15.85,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't mind, no matter \Nwhat he did to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:18.94,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it was all for my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.59,0:18:21.43,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,But he
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:25.66,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,went to my wife in the hospital \Nand demanded repayment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:29.59,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,My wife became despondent, and \Nher condition suddenly worsened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:33.80,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Her last words were “I'm sorry.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.81,0:18:41.93,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I remember you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:45.93,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we'd met before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.17,0:18:49.34,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you're the boy who came to my store.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:50.44,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.81,0:18:54.40,DCItalic,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Who dropped this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:56.32,DCItalic,GIRL A,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.28,0:19:08.54,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who dropped the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.92,0:19:10.75,DCItalic,BOY C,0000,0000,0000,,I-It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.75,0:19:12.21,DCItalic,BOY C,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't make up stories!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:14.51,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:17.38,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,See the footprints on that stool?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.86,0:19:21.00,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit stood on that so \Nthey could pick up the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.42,0:19:23.64,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the footprints \Nof a boy's athletic shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:26.56,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So we can eliminate the girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.13,0:19:30.45,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The remaining three boys are \Nall wearing athletic shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.45,0:19:34.40,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But the dirt on the stool \Nis damp and viscous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.84,0:19:37.32,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't from the schoolyard, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:38.89,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.89,0:19:40.95,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The dirt from the shrine out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.63,0:19:44.44,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The dirt on your shoes is dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.44,0:19:45.94,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.32,0:19:48.12,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So you couldn't have done it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:50.48,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You're tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.48,0:19:53.32,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have needed the \Nstool to get the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:19:57.26,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves only you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.96,0:20:00.09,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.44,0:20:04.97,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you going after him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.16,0:20:07.04,DCItalic,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:08.85,DCItalic,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,He'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:09.92,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:12.87,DCItalic,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,I trust that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.87,0:20:14.97,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But the engine is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.42,0:20:17.73,DCItalic,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,If something's broken, \Nyou just have to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.02,0:20:29.43,DCItalic,BOY C,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.01,0:20:39.34,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,My late wife used to talk \Nabout that day all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.01,0:20:45.72,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.60,0:20:49.80,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed at \Nall since ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:51.86,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:23.54,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If he goes to the police now, \Nhe can still turn himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:27.18,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You went awfully easy on \Nthe culprit this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.44,0:21:29.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.78,0:22:57.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:01.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun, go to Nagai-san's \Nstore immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.66,0:23:02.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.44,0:23:05.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sato-kun, look into Kuromaru Finance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.53,0:23:07.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If they're actually giving out dubious loans,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.76,0:23:09.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to investigate them thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.76,0:23:10.87,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.16,0:23:13.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Nagai-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.73,0:23:15.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,come with me to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.91,0:23:16.91,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.10,0:23:21.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I shouldn't ask, but \Nwhy did you turn yourself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.78,0:23:25.55,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious boy appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:27.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.08,0:23:28.97,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.97,0:23:33.26,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,a mysterious boy who hadn't changed \Nat all since ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.69,0:23:34.68,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,He...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.96,0:23:42.88,DCMain,NAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,He may have been sent by my wife in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.80,0:23:47.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.57,0:23:52.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this forest seem like there \Nwould actually be zombies out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.71,0:23:58.12,DCMain,RIA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is the magical sword
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.12,0:24:01.19,DCMain,RIA,0000,0000,0000,,that turns zombies to ash \Nat the slightest touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.54,0:24:03.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Harawaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:09.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just leave already!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,A Cottage Surrounded By Zombies \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.77,0:24:14.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is “A Cottage \NSurrounded By Zombies, Part One!”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:35.07,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Zombie Blade
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:32.90,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:35.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A zombie blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:36.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ran, you can be such an airhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:40.08,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.76,0:24:37.74,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.74,0:24:39.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You can practically count on it.
